{
  "text": "Microtomography provides anatomic detail at a resolution (150 mm to up to 1 mm) not available with conventional CT technology, typically ranging between 2 mm and 400 mm. It has previously been applied to high-resolution visualization of aneurysm stents. 10 11 There has been relatively little application of microtomography to the accurate modeling of intracranial aneurysm coils, [CITATION_1] and no previous reports of applying microtomography from a high energy synchrotron beam to reduce the coils' beam-hardening artifact. We studied the difference between the homogeneous porous medium approach to coil modeling in CFD and CFD incorporating high-resolution synchrotron X-ray microtomographic imaging of coils deployed inside three-dimensional (3D) printed in vitro aneurysmal models.",
